page.title: 01TYDD ST. GILES- GAZETEER
page.content: The block is in the north of The Fens,and the county boundary between Cambridgeshire and Lincolnshire runs through it. The area thus contains part of the parish of Tydd St. Mary in Lincolnshire, and the parish of Tydd St.Giles in Cambridgeshire. Tydd St. Giles is a small village of about 900 people. It is situated about 6 miles NW of the market town of Wisbech, and about 16 miles W of the port of Kings Lynn.The marshes on the edge of The Wash are about 10 miles away.The River Nene runs about 2 miles to the E.
